    Restrict map panning to an area

    This source code of this example is adapted from the MapLibre GL JS example - Restrict map panning to an area .

    Uncomment the following line to install leafmap if needed.

    In[1]:
    Copied! 
    # %pip install "leafmap[maplibre]"
    # %pip install "leafmap[maplibre]"
    In[2]:
    Copied! 
    import os
import leafmap.maplibregl as leafmap
    import os import leafmap.maplibregl as leafmap

    To run this notebook, you will need an API key from MapTiler. Once you have the API key, you can set it as an environment variable in your notebook or script as follows:

    In[3]:
    Copied! 
    # os.environ["MAPTILER_KEY"] = "YOUR_API_KEY"
    # os.environ["MAPTILER_KEY"] = "YOUR_API_KEY"
    In[4]:
    Copied! 
    MAPTILER_KEY = leafmap.get_api_key("MAPTILER_KEY")
style = f"https://api.maptiler.com/maps/streets/style.json?key={MAPTILER_KEY}"
    MAPTILER_KEY = leafmap.get_api_key("MAPTILER_KEY") style = f"https://api.maptiler.com/maps/streets/style.json?key={MAPTILER_KEY}"
    In[5]:
    Copied! 
    bounds = [
    [-74.04728500751165, 40.68392799015035],
    [-73.91058699000139, 40.87764500765852],
]
    bounds = [ [-74.04728500751165, 40.68392799015035], [-73.91058699000139, 40.87764500765852], ]
    In[6]:
    Copied! 
    m = leafmap.Map(center=[-73.9978, 40.7209], zoom=13, max_bounds=bounds, style=style)
m
    m = leafmap.Map(center=[-73.9978, 40.7209], zoom=13, max_bounds=bounds, style=style) m
